00:25.120 --> 00:29.180
The Gospel of Mark, Chapter Three.

00:29.980 --> 00:36.980
And he entered again into the synagogue, and there was a man there with a withered hand.

00:37.400 --> 00:46.380
And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the Sabbath day, that they might accuse him.

00:46.380 --> 00:52.440
And he said unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.

00:52.900 --> 00:59.080
And he sayeth unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the Sabbath days,

00:59.520 --> 01:06.740
Or to do evil, to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.

01:07.380 --> 01:14.340
And when he had looked round about on them, With anger being grieved

01:14.340 --> 01:21.020
For the hardness of their hearts, he sayeth unto the man, Stretch forth thine hand.

01:21.580 --> 01:27.200
And he stretched it out, and his hand was restored whole as the other.

01:27.640 --> 01:34.380
And the Pharisees went forth and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him,

01:34.520 --> 01:40.600
How they might destroy him. But Jesus withdrew himself with his disciples

01:40.600 --> 01:47.320
to the sea, and a great multitude from Galilee followed him, and from Judea,

01:48.100 --> 01:53.760
and from Jerusalem, and from Edomia, and from beyond Jordan.

01:54.260 --> 01:59.180
And they about Tyree and Sidon, a great multitude,

01:59.680 --> 02:05.000
when they had heard what great things he did, came unto him.

02:05.000 --> 02:12.600
And he spake to his disciples that a small ship should wait on him because of the multitude,

02:13.300 --> 02:17.960
lest they should throng him. For he had healed many,

02:18.420 --> 02:25.560
insomuch that they pressed upon him, for to touch him as many as had plagues.

02:26.040 --> 02:30.100
And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him,

02:30.100 --> 02:38.160
and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of God. And he straightly charged them that they should not

02:38.160 --> 02:45.980
make him known. And he goeth up into a mountain, and calleth unto him whom he would.

02:46.180 --> 02:53.280
And they came unto him, and he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might

02:53.280 --> 03:01.620
send them forth to preach, and to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils.

03:02.060 --> 03:09.260
And Simon he surnamed Peter, and James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James,

03:09.380 --> 03:17.360
he surnamed them Boangres, which is the sons of thunder. And Andrew and Philip,

03:17.360 --> 03:24.580
and Bartholomew, and Matthew and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddeus,

03:24.860 --> 03:32.500
and Simon the Canaanite, and Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him.

03:33.320 --> 03:40.180
And they went into in-house, and the multitude cometh together again, so that they could not

03:40.180 --> 03:47.320
much as eat bread. And when his friends heard of it, they went out to lay hold on him.

03:47.580 --> 03:55.020
And they said, He is beside himself. And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said,

03:55.360 --> 04:02.940
He hath bells above, and by the prints of devils casteth he out devils. And he called them unto

04:02.940 --> 04:12.140
him, and saith unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan? And if a kingdom be divided

04:12.140 --> 04:20.960
against itself, that kingdom cannot stand. And if a house be divided against itself, that house

04:21.460 --> 04:29.160
cannot stand. And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand,

04:29.160 --> 04:36.820
but hath an end. No man can enter into a strong man's house, and spoil his goods,

04:37.460 --> 04:45.800
except he will first bind the strong man. And then he will spoil his house. Verily I say unto you,

04:46.020 --> 04:54.380
All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies, wherewith soever they shall

04:54.380 --> 05:03.940
blaspheme. But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Ghost hath never forgiveness, but is in

05:03.940 --> 05:14.020
danger of eternal damnation, because they said, He hath an unclean spirit. There came then his

05:14.020 --> 05:20.260
brethren and his mother, and standing without, sent unto him, calling him. And the multitude

05:20.260 --> 05:27.820
said about him, and they said unto him, Behold thy mother and thy brethren without seek for thee.

05:28.420 --> 05:36.780
And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother or my brethren? And he looked round about on them,

05:37.140 --> 05:46.400
which said about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren. For whosoever shall do the will

05:46.400 --> 05:53.100
of God the same as my brother, and my sister, and my mother.

05:54.060 --> 06:01.940
Chapter 4 And he began again to teach by the seaside, and there was gathered unto him a

06:01.940 --> 06:10.140
great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and set in the sea. And the whole multitude was

06:10.140 --> 06:17.160
gathered by the sea on the land. And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them

06:17.160 --> 06:26.680
in his doctrine, Hearken, behold, there went out a sower to sow. And it came to pass, as he sowed,

06:26.820 --> 06:34.720
some fell by the wayside, and the fowls of the air came, and devoured it up. And some fell on

06:34.720 --> 06:42.280
stony ground, where it had not much earth, and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth

06:42.280 --> 06:50.260
of earth. But when the sun was up, it was scorched, and because it had no root, it withered away.

06:50.800 --> 06:58.120
And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.

06:58.750 --> 07:07.340
And other fell on good ground, and did yield fruit, and sprang up, and increased, and brought forth

07:07.340 --> 07:16.440
some thirty, and some sixty, and some in hundred. And he said unto them, He that hath ears to hear,

07:17.040 --> 07:25.860
let him hear. And when he was alone, they that were about him with the twelve, asked of him the

07:25.860 --> 07:33.800
parable. And he said unto them, Unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God,

07:34.060 --> 07:42.640
but unto them that are without, all these things are done in parables. That seeing they may see,

07:42.880 --> 07:51.660
and not perceive, and hearing they may hear, and not understand, lest at any time they should be

07:51.660 --> 08:00.160
converted, and their sins should be forgiven them. And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable?

08:00.600 --> 08:10.680
And how then will ye know all parables? The sower soweth the word, and these are they by the wayside,

08:10.980 --> 08:18.580
where the word is sown. But when they have heard, Satan cometh immediately, and taketh away the word

08:18.580 --> 08:26.700
that was sown in their hearts. And these are they likewise which are sown on stony ground,

08:27.120 --> 08:33.540
who when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness, and have no root in

08:33.540 --> 08:41.440
themselves, and so endure but for a time. Afterward, when affliction or persecution ariseth,

08:41.440 --> 08:49.760
for the word's sake, immediately they are offended. And these are they which are sown among thorns,

08:50.960 --> 08:57.300
such as hear the word, and the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches,

08:57.760 --> 09:05.380
and the lust of other things entering in choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.

09:06.080 --> 09:14.960
And these are they which are sown on good ground, such as hear the word, and receive it,

09:15.120 --> 09:23.240
and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some in hundred. And he said unto them,

09:23.620 --> 09:32.180
Is a candle brought to be put under a bush, or under a bed, and not to be set on a candlestick?

09:32.960 --> 09:39.540
For there is nothing hid which shall not be manifested, neither was there anything kept

09:39.540 --> 09:48.700
secret but that it should come abroad. If any man hath ears to hear, let him hear. And he said unto

09:48.700 --> 09:56.120
them, Take heed what ye hear, with what measure ye meet it shall be measured to you, and unto you

09:56.120 --> 10:05.760
hear shall more be given. For he that hath to him shall be given, and he that hath not from him

10:05.760 --> 10:15.000
shall be taken even that which he hath. And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man

10:15.000 --> 10:23.760
should cast seed into the ground, and should sleep and rise night and day, and the seed should

10:23.760 --> 10:30.120
spring and grow up. He knoweth not how. For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself,

10:30.640 --> 10:39.880
first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear. But when the fruit is

10:39.880 --> 10:47.040
brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come. And he said,

10:47.040 --> 10:55.020
Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God, or with what comparison shall we compare it?

10:55.600 --> 11:03.700
It is like a grain of mustard seed, which when it is sown in the earth is less than all the seeds

11:03.700 --> 11:12.080
that be in the earth. But when it is sown it groweth up, and becomeeth greater than all herbs,

11:12.080 --> 11:19.180
and shooteth out great branches, so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.

11:19.760 --> 11:27.040
And with many such parables spake he the word unto them, as they were able to hear it.

11:27.780 --> 11:35.560
But without a parable spake he not unto them, and when they were alone he expounded all things

11:35.560 --> 11:43.260
to his disciples. And the same day when the even was come, he sayeth unto them,

11:43.560 --> 11:50.920
Let us pass over on to the other side. And when they had sent away the multitude,

11:51.420 --> 11:59.700
they took him even as he was in the ship, and there were also with him other little ships.

11:59.700 --> 12:08.640
And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the ship, so that it was now full.

12:08.980 --> 12:15.780
And he was in the hinder part of the ship, asleep on a pillow. And they awake him,

12:16.080 --> 12:25.960
and say unto him, Master, carest thou not that we perish? And he arose and rebuked the wind,

12:25.960 --> 12:34.600
and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.

12:35.280 --> 12:41.900
And he said unto them, Why are ye so fearful? How is it that ye have no faith?

12:42.460 --> 12:49.200
And they feared exceedingly, and said one to another, What manner of man is this,

12:49.200 --> 12:53.580
that even the wind and the sea obey him?

